<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Calls For Full Economic Review </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802144894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1302 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0802144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl has called 
for a general stocktaking in society at the forum "Safeguarding 
Germany as a business and investment location" in Bonn today. 
Even an improved economic situation, which is already emerging, 
cannot alone remove the structural failings of past years, the 
chancellor stressed. Important reforms, such as the reform of 
the railways and the postal service, have been delayed for 
decades. At the same time, during the good years unions and 
employers nowhere near managed to exploit to the full the legal 
scope for more flexible working hours and longer machine running 
times. 
  Kohl described as a priority "completing economic and social 
unity in Germany." The people in eastern Germany today are 
going through a "difficult and far-reaching structural change at 
a breathtaking pace." Much less radical changes in western 
Germany would put people very much on the defensive, he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

