<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sees Reason for `Realistic Optimism' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902142594 Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG in German 9 Feb 94 
p 25 </F>

<F P=103> AU0902142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "Th.": "Kohl Sees Reason for `Realistic </F>
Optimism'"] 
  [Text] Bonn -- "I am quite pleased that confidence is 
growing." With these words Chancellor Helmut Kohl commented on 
the recession at the forum "Safeguarding Germany as a Business 
and Investment Location," organized by Economics Minister 
Guenther Rexrodt in Bonn. The majority of the structural 
problems that we have to settle today have "nothing whatsoever" 
to do with German unity. In the next tax reform, clear priority 
must be given to families with children. Safeguarding Germany's 
attractiveness as a business location includes improving the 
climate for progress and technology, Kohl pointed out. The 
chancellor sees reason for "realistic optimism." Rexrodt 
stressed that the inflexibility that is currently prevailing 
might ultimately mean the end. [as published] 

</TEXT>

