<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt Says Fighting Unemployment Top Task </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802142194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1145 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0802142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Federal Economics Minister Guenter 
Rexrodt has described the fight against unemployment as "the 
government's most important goal." The fact that over four 
million of their fellow citizens do not have jobs is one of the 
greatest challenges for society and the state, since the 
founding of the Federal Republic, Rexrodt said today in response 
to the latest labor market figures from Nuremberg. This is not 
one of the usual economic crises, but "a deep structural crisis." 
  Rexrodt resolutely rejected "political demagogues" with 
"patent prescriptions." Rather, it is necessary to embark "upon 
the stony path of structural renewal." 
  The economics minister called upon companies and unions to 
keep a sense of perspective in pay disputes. "Both sides in the 
current [engineering] pay dispute can signal common sense." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

