<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troops To Leave In March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802211994 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1900 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri has confirmed that the 
Italian contingent in Somalia will be withdrawn by the end of 
March. Fabbri also said he is worried by the worsening of the 
conflict between the Somali factions. 
  [Begin Fabbri recording] The army and defense chiefs of 
staff 
have planned our homecoming in agreement with UNOSOM [UN 
Operation in Somalia] and have taken the needs of the other 
contingents, such as the German one, into consideration, in 
order to be able to guarantee an environment of maximum security. 
  In order to verify from the ground that everything is 
proceeding according to plan, today I made arrangements for a 
mission [as heard] under the command of Deputy Chief of Staff 
General Zoldan. I have confirmed that a naval flotilla will be 
sent offshore near Mogadishu, and that aircraft will be 
redeployed in Nairobi. We are doing everything we can think of 
to guarantee maximum security during the withdrawal phase. The 
mission is practically over. There are some technical time 
limits which are obligatory in relation to agreements that we 
have made with the United Nations. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

