<H3> <TI>   Government `Reserved' on Denktas' `Sincerity' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0702183394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0702183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government maintains an extremely reserved 
position on Rauf Denktas' sincerity and believes that its fears, 
which have already been conveyed to the UN secretary general, 
should be erased by the Turkish Cypriot leader himself during 
the talks. This came out in a statement this morning by the 
government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis, who stressed that 
President Kliridhis is still awaiting clarifications he 
requested through his letter to the UN secretary general. 
  Mr. Kasoulidhis recalled that in the past too, Denktas 
appeared to have accepted some things, while in practice it was 
established that this had not been the case. 
  Mr. Kasoulidhis further noted that at the president's 
private 
meetings with the political leaders, DISI [Democratic Rally], 
AKEL [Restorative Party of the Working People], and DIKO 
[Democratic Party] maintained that the Greek Cypriot side cannot 
refuse to go to the talks. 

</TEXT>

