<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   European Council's Finsberg Departs Following Contacts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0502153494 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1130 GMT 5 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0502153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lord Finsberg, rapporteur for the Cyprus problem to 
the Political Affairs Committee of the Council of Europe 
Parliamentary Assembly, has stated that he observed a sincere 
goodwill on the part of the Turkish Cypriots with regard to 
assisting the UN secretary general in his efforts to assemble 
the confidence-building measures package. Lord Finsberg left 
the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus [TRNC] after concluding 
his contacts. 
  In a statement he issued to TAK [Turkish Cypriot News 
Agency], Lord Finsberg stressed that he had observed 
considerable goodwill on the Turkish side. Stating that 
constructive and useful exchange of views were conducted while 
he was in the TRNC, Finsberg said he observed that the Turkish 
side assisted the UN secretary general in assembling the 
confidence-building measures. 
  Stating that north Cyprus would benefit from successful 
negotiations, Finsberg stressed that he encountered the same 
goodwill in north Cyprus as he did in south Cyprus. Reiterating 
his decision to advise the COE Parliamentary Assembly members in 
favor of hearing the Turkish Cypriots' voice, Lord Finsberg 
added that work will be undertaken to enable the TRNC political 
party leaders' participation in the parliamentary assembly. 
  Reiterating that it is impossible to fill the chair 
representing the Turkish side for the time being, Lord Finsberg 
added that he believes that the TRNC political party leaders 
will be invited to the parliamentary assembly once progress is 
made on the confidence-building measures and on a solution to 
the Cyprus issue. 

</TEXT>

