<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas on Conditions for Entering European Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802184894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1600 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0802184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Lefkose], Feb 8 (AA) -- President Rauf Denktas of the 
Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus said on Tuesday [8 February] 
that the whole of Cyprus can not enter to European Union (EU) 
before we say "yes." 
  Denktas, evaluating EU's message to Greek Cypriots which 
said 
if the concerned sides reach an agreement, pre-studies will 
begin on Cyprus' membership to the EU, said the two sides living 
in Cyprus should hold separate referendums on the issue and 
should apply for the Union's membership. 
  Denktas answering questions on the issue said accepting 
Greek 
Cypriots as the responsible "nation" was a mistake adding that 
the whole Cyprus cannot enter to EU before an agreement between 
the two sides. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

