<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kotak Decides To Wage Anti-British Campaign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802143594 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1130 GMT 8 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0802143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Free Democratic Party [FDP] has decided to wage 
a campaign against Britain due to that country's stand toward 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and Cyprus. 
  In a statement he issued today, FDP leader Ismet Kotak said 
that his party wants Britain, which is on the side of the 
wrongdoers in Cyprus and Bosnia-Herzegovina, to get up and leave 
the bases in Cyprus. Kotak urged the Turkish Cypriot people to 
take a stand against every British action in Cyprus, stressing 
that there is no room for a third state in Cyprus. 
  The FDP leader pointed out that the world must condemn the 
stand before clear massacres of those who are opposed to the 
Muslims in Bosnia-Herzegovina and Cyprus. He urged the world to 
protest the present British Government. 

</TEXT>

