<H3> <TI>   New National Guard Commander Assumes Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0702104994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0800 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0702104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General Nikolaos Vorvolakos today assumed 
the leadership of the National Guard stressing that he knows the 
responsibility he undertakes. 
  Arriving this morning at the National Guard General Staff, 
Lt. Gen. Vorvolakos was honored by a military unit and the 
military band. He was welcomed by National Guard Deputy Chief 
Lieutenant General Ioannis Fotiadhis. 
  In a statement, Vorvolakos said his mission was not 
difficult, but very responsible. Referring to the Greece-Cyprus 
unified defense doctrine, Vorvolakos said it is the privilege 
and responsibility of his political superiors. He said: I just 
execute the decisions. 

</TEXT>

