<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denies Human Rights Violations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0302181394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1600 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0302181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on a recent statement by the Turkish 
Foreign Ministry alternate spokesman accusing our country of 
alleged violation of the Muslim minority's human rights, Foreign 
Ministry spokesman Kostandinos Bikas said that the government 
condemns Turkey's attempt to intervene in Greek decisionmaking. 
  The spokesman said: Greece is a just state and fully 
respects human rights. Turkey is neither concerned nor 
interested in alleged violations of the Muslim minority's human 
rights in Greece. It is merely seeking excuses, encouraging 
nationalistic extremism, distorting situations and facts, and 
unhesitatingly using the minority issue, obviously realizing the 
damage done to Greek-Turkish relations and stability in the 
region. 

</TEXT>

