<H3> <TI>   German Bundestag President Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0702084794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 0800 
GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0702084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] German Bundestag President Rita Sussmuth arrived in 
Turkey on an official visit last night. Sussmuth and the 
parliamentary delegation accompanying her were received at 
Esenboga Airport by Husamettin Cindoruk, speaker of the Turkish 
Grand National Assembly. 
  In a statement at the airport, Sussmuth said that 
interparliamentary contacts are very useful at a time when 
Europe is going through a process of change. The talks to be 
held in Turkey within this framework will make important 
contributions, she said. Sussmuth stressed that Turkish-German 
friendship is multifaceted, adding that Germany's aim is to 
ensure that the 2 million Turks living in Germany are happy. 
  (Thomas Kosanli), head of the Turkish-German Parliamentary 
Friendship Group, stressed that the intensive cooperation 
between the parliaments of the two countries is important for 
the future of the two peoples. 
  In turn, Cindoruk said that Sussmuth's visit will be 
extremely constructive for the development of the relations 
between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

