<H3> <TI>   Germany's Suessmuth Visits President Demirel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802184594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1540 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0802184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 8 (A.A) -- German Parliament Speaker 
Rita Suessmuth and a delegation accompanying her visited 
President Suleyman Demirel, it was reported on Tuesday [8 
February]. 
  Demirel, during the meeting, said indefiniteness continue 
throughout the world after the Cold War. 
  Demirel said new conditions appeared after this time put 
pressure on international organizations adding that these 
organizations have difficulty in meeting the new demands. 
  He said the tragedy in Bosnia-Herzegovina could cause 
serious 
problems if it continued. 
  The president said Turkish-German relations on the fields of 
economy and tourism improved a lot in the recent years adding 
that relations between the two country parliaments were 
im?ortant within this framework. 
  Demirel also said Turkey was pleased with the ban put by 
Germany on the outlawed separatist terrorist organization. 

</TEXT>

