<H3> <TI>   Bosnia's Drakovic Meets With Minister Cevheri </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802144894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0802144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] State Minister Necmettin Cevheri has said that 
Turkey is determined not to leave Bosnia-Herzegovina alone in 
the midst of the Christian world. 
  Cevheri was speaking at a meeting with Enest Drakovic, 
Bosnian minister of education, science, culture, and sports. 
Cevheri stressed that Turkey displays its stand at every 
opportunity. He pointed out that the death of 68 people as a 
result of a Serbian artillery attack on Sarajevo deeply wounded 
the Turkish people, adding: We know that grieving is not 
enough. We will continue to be on the side of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina with whatever is necessary and with all the 
possible means. 
  Drakovic said, in turn, that the ties between the peoples of 
the two countries go back in history, and asked for Turkey's 
help in preparing an Islamic encyclopedia. 

</TEXT>

