<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Culture Minister Fikri Saglar has said that the 
time has come for the world to renounce its double standard 
toward Bosnia-Herzegovina and take action. 
  Enest Drakovic, Bosnian minister of education, science, 
culture and sports, concluded his contacts in Turkey and 
returned to his country this evening. He was seen off at 
Esenboga Airport by Saglar, who criticized the fact that the 
Western world has remained indifferent to the massacre of 
thousands of people in Bosnia-Herzegovina and called on the 
world to take immediate action in Bosnia-Herzegovina and lift 
the arms embargo. 
  Drakovic said that the agreements reached during his 
contacts 
in Turkey constitute sound foundations for future cooperation 
between the two countries. 

