<H3> <TI>   Government Reportedly To Buy More Russian Helicopters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0802220894 Istanbul SABAH in Turkish 4 Feb 94 p 23 </F>
<F P=103> NC0802220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul SABAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Turkey will purchase 19 MI-17 helicopters from 
Tatarstan. The helicopters will be assigned to the General 
Command of the Gendarmerie Forces. It has been ascertained that 
the talks on the purchase of the helicopters have entered their 
final stage. In a statement to INTERFAX, Aleksandr Lavrentyev, 
director of Russia's most important helicopter manufacturing 
installations in Tatarstan, has said that Turkey decided to 
purchase 19 MI-8 and MI-17 helicopters for its gendarmerie 
forces in 1993. Stressing that another Turkish delegation 
visited Kazan early in January, Lavrentyev said that it held 
talks for the purchase of several more helicopters in addition 
to those that Turkey planned to buy for $65,000,000. 
  The helicopters Turkey will buy for its gendarmerie forces 
are capable of flying 225 km per hour. They can fly and land on 
any terrain 4,000 meters above sea level. 

</TEXT>

