<H4>   Italy Says Ultimatum `Step Forward' </H4>
<F P=102> LD0902231994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 2259 GMT 
9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902231994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] "It is a first, significant step forward in sorting 
out the affair." This is how Foreign Minister Andreatta 
commented on the Bosnia ultimatum decided by the NATO Council. 
  Andreatta, who is attending the Geneva conference of 
countries bordering the former Yugoslavia, added: "There are 
still some unanswered questions." He cited problems concerning 
the international administration of Sarajevo, disarmament, and 
the coexistence of different ethnic groups in single districts 
of Sarajevo. 

</TEXT>

