<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO Participants Comment on Bosnia Declaration, Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Move Toward Peace' </H4>
<F P=102> LD0902231394 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 2230 GMT 
9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902231394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A few minutes ago, as soon as NATO's demand that 
Bosnian Serbs lift the siege of Sarajevo was made public, 
Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana said in a statement to 
Radio Nacional that contrary to what one might think, warning of 
air strikes is a move toward peace. 
  [Begin Solana recording] It is a decision that is, or 
should, 
be understood in the context of a peace process. The logic that 
all of us are still backing is the logic of peace, not the logic 
of war. Unfortunately, what is happening is that sometimes one 
has to threaten with a specific military action, with a concrete 
one, one that has a specific timeframe and in a specific area to 
reach one's aim, peace, so that it happens more rapidly. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

