<H3> <TI>   EC Considering Sanctions Against Croatia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1002075794 Paris AFP in English 0052 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1002075794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Copenhagen, Feb 10 (AFP) -- Danish Foreign Minister 
Niels Helveg Petersen said Wednesday [9 February] the European 
Community "still envisages introducing sanctions against 
Croatia" because of its involvement in the Bosnian conflict. 
  Petersen told a press conference he had raised the question 
of sanctions against the Croats at a meeting in Brussels Monday 
of European Community foreign ministers, but added that the 
matter had been sidelined by the massacre in Sarajevo and 
discussions on airstrikes against the Bosnian Serbs. 
  "The member states agree that the question of sanctions will 
be discussed soon," he said. "What we are looking at is either 
trade sanctions or, alternatively, the possibility of 
withdrawing the preferential status Croatia enjoys in its trade 
with the Community." 

</TEXT>

