<H3> <TI>   Pakistan Raises Kashmir at UN Human Rights Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0702133394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0702133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has again urged India to hold plebiscite 
in occupied Kashmir and to allow the Kashmiri people to decide 
their future by themselves. Addressing the Human Rights 
Commission meeting in Geneva, the leader of the Pakistan 
delegation, Mr. Iqbal Akhund, said the only possible solution to 
the Kashmir dispute is the one which is acceptable to the people 
of Kashmir. He said that it will bring peace to the people of 
the subcontinent and strengthen the forces of democracy and 
progress in Pakistan and India. The Pakistan delegate said that 
over the last 45 years, India has maintained its occupation of 
occupied Kashmir, but has been unable to win the support of the 
Kashmiri people. At present, there are 600,000 Indian troops in 
occupied Kashmir engaged in suppressing the popular uprising 
against Indian occupation. 

</TEXT>

