Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Robert Raymond Appointed Director </F>
General of European Monetary Institute -- EMI"; as released by 
Brussels TEXTLINE database] 
  [Text] The Council of the European Monetary Institute, 
which met on Tuesday [8 February], appointed Mr. Robert Raymond 
director general of the new institute. Mr. Raymond, age 60, is 
presently director general for credit at the Bank of France. 
The EMI Council also appointed the directors of three of the 
five departments set up in the EMI. Dutchman Mr. G.P.J. 
Hogeweg, director-coordinator at the Netherlands' Central Bank, 
was appointed Director of the Department of Economics and 
Statistics; Mr. Hanspeter K. Scheller, of the Secretariat of EC 
governors, will be responsible for the Secretariat General; Mr. 
J.S. Etherington, of the Bank of England, will head the 
Communications Systems and Information Department. The EMI 
Council is made up of the twelve governors of the European Union 
and its president, Mr. Alexandre Lamfalussy. 

