<H3> <TI>   Swiss Foreign Minister Comments on EU Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202105394 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 0900 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Swiss foreign minister Flavio Cotti says there 
is no alternative for Switzerland than to eventually join the 
European Union [EU]. Mr. Cotti, speaking at Zurich University, 
said such problems in Europe as crime, transport, and 
environmental policies could no longer be solved on a national 
or regional basis. He said the EU was still far from being a 
perfect organization, but was already a crucial guarantor for 
regional stability. 

</TEXT>

