<H3> <TI>   Daily Views NATO Ultimatum to Bosnian Serbs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1002111294 Vienna KURIER in German 10 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1002111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Rau" commentary: "The Ultimatum"] </F>
  [Text] Aggressors only understand the language of 
violence. As soon as it became clear that NATO was heading for 
an ultimatum to the murderous Serbian gunners around Sarajevo, 
the Bosnian Serbs speedily prepared to withdraw their heavy 
weapons before the adoption of a resolution. Here only the 
threat with the ultimatum worked. For the time being. If the 
pressure on the Serbs decreases again, they will again strike 
like birds of prey that have been driven away. On the other 
hand, the Muslims want more than only not to be massacred any 
longer. This is Clinton's hour. He worked toward the 
ultimatum. At full risk: His presidency can be destroyed if he 
gets dragged into a Balkan war. This will surely be the case if 
the threat with the ultimatum is not implemented. Aggressors 
only understand the language of violence -- if the preparedness 
for action is behind it. 

</TEXT>

