<H3> <TI>   Brinkman To Combat Illegal Entry of Foreigners </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0902154194 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD in Dutch 8 Feb 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> BR0902154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Brinkman: Root Out Illegal Entry of </F>
Foreigners"] 
  [Excerpt] The Hague -- During a speech delivered yesterday 
evening in Apeldoorn, L.C. Brinkman, who heads the CDA 
[Christian Democratic Appeal] list of candidates, feels that 
illegal foreigners "must be rooted out." In order to prevent 
illegals from entering the Netherlands, foreigners, as it were, 
must be checked on the ramp to the airplane before it departs 
for the Netherlands, Brinkman said. 
  According to Brinkman, a "precise" asylum policy is needed 
in 
order to prevent Netherlanders from blaming foreigners for all 
their problems. If we are clear about who is rightly here, 
Brinkman said, than nobody has the right to say "You don't 
belong here." 
  The tone of Brinkman's speech elicited criticism from 
coalition partner, the PvdA [Labor Party]. M. van Traa (of the 
PvdA), a member of the Lower House, spoke of "a mistaken use of 
words. You only use the term `root out' in connection with 
weeds. On this subject matter, you must pay close attention to 
your choice of words. Politicians have to understand that." 
According to van Traa, illegality is not to be totally 
discouraged, "unless you want to build a wall around the 
country. You must therefore fight illegality where it causes 
the most trouble, for instance within the context of 
criminality." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

