  [Text] London, Feb 10 (AFP) -- Two British MPs have been 
taken hostage in Somalia, the Foreign Office said Thursday [10 
February]. 
  Early reports said the two MPs had been accompanying a 
private humanitarian mission when they were captured. 
  The Foreign Office gave no further details on their identity 
nor the spot where they were taken. 

