<H3> <TI>   Comments on Agreements, Karabakh Peacekeepers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1002091294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1002091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev has said that 
the work on exploiting the Azerbaijani oil fields will be 
concluded this month and that Turkey will also participate in 
the agreements to be concluded on the issue. 
  Replying to questions by a Turkish Radio and Television 
correspondent, Aliyev said that he does not foresee any changes 
regarding Turkey's share in the agreement. Pointing out that 
there are various oil pipeline projects, Aliyev added, however, 
that in most of these projects having the pipeline cross Turkey 
is a high consideration. 
  He noted that Azerbaijan's relations with Russia are 
continuing on their normal course but that the cease-fire plan 
that has been proposed was not found suitable. Aliyev stated 
that Azerbaijan will be deciding on which countries might 
participate in the peacekeeping forces to be stationed in 
Karabakh and that his country wants Turkey to participate in 
these forces. He noted that the unconditional withdrawal of 
Armenian forces from occupied Azerbaijani territory is the first 
condition for a possible peace agreement with the Armenians. 

</TEXT>

