<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Transportation Agreement Signed with Romania, Bulgaria </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1002093094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2000 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1002093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Turkey, Romania, and Bulgaria have decided to 
establish a permanent working group to following the 
developments in the field of transportation. An agreement on 
the issue was signed in Ankara by Transportation Minister Mehmet 
Kostepen, Romanian Transportation Minister Paul Teororu, and 
Bulgarian Transportation Minister Kiril Ermenkov. 
  In a statement at the signing ceremony, Kostepen said that 
the developments in the Balkans have increased the importance of 
the cooperation among the three countries. He added that with 
this agreement various measures have been adopted in a bid to 
make the transportation among the three countries safer and 
faster. Kostepen said that the three countries have also 
decided to take steps to once more regulate Danube 
transportation and delineate the Black Sea air space and FIR 
[Flight Information Region] line. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

