<F P=102>  AU1002104294 Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE in German 
10 Feb 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU1002104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "ank": "New Warning Strikes in Metal </F>
Industry"] 
  [Text] Frankfurt/Main, 9 Feb -- On Wednesday [9 February] 
the IG-Metall trade union continued the warning strikes in the 
western German metal industry with strikes in 228 companies. 
The focal points of the rallies were in North Rhine-Westphalia, 
Baden-Wuerttemberg, and Hesse. According to the trade union, 
about 119,000 metalworkers participated in the actions. This 
Thursday and Friday the IG-Metall will not be able to keep its 
warning strikes up to the same extent, since in many regions of 
western Germany Karneval is being celebrated, IG-Metall Chairman 
Zwickel said. On the weekend the leaders of the employers and 
the trade union plan to discuss a solution to the wage conflict. 

