Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Addressing a ground-breaking 
ceremony in Izmir, Murat Karayalcin, state minister and deputy 
prime minister, said that in the wake of the latest Serbian 
attack in Bosnia-Herzegovina, Turkey made requests in NATO for 
an intervention. He added: 
  [Begin Karayalcin recording] Those who are our friends, 
those who are our allies, if they want to continue with their 
friendship and alliance with Turkey, this is their chance. They 
must take it. They must decide to intervene on the Serbian 
artillery positions in the hills around Sarajevo. They must end 
this massacre. Turkey will assess this. It might assess it 
today or in the future. If Turkey's friendship, the Turkish 
people's friendship, is important for the Western forces, they 
have an opportunity to show it. Let them show their friendship. 
In turn, we will show our friendship. From now on, we will 
display this determined stand regarding Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
[end recording] [passage omitted] 

