Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finland's participation in NATO's Partnership for 
Peace program is likely to be restricted to peacekeeping 
training in the initial stage. According to Foreign Minister 
Heikki Haavisto, Finland will study the matter during the spring 
and will have talks both with NATO countries and neutral 
countries about the Partnership for Peace offer. Haavisto 
