<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Norbert Rief: "Austria To Train Inspectors for </F>
Chemical Weapons"] 
  [Excerpt] Vienna -- Austria will now once more participate 
in an international peacekeeping program. At the Seibersdorf 
research center, in Lower Austria, UN personnel of the 
Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) will 
be trained this year to inspect civilian chemical plants. The 
OPCW inspectors should thus be able to ascertain whether 
chemical weapons are being or can be produced in chemical 
plants. [passage omitted] 

