<F P=100> UNITED KINGDOM </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Investigate Azerbaijan Arms Claims </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1002181294 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 1603 GMT 10 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1002181294 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By PRESS ASSOCIATION Lords staff] </F>
  [Text] The Government was investigating reports that 
British arms and mercenaries were being used by Azerbaijan in 
its conflict with the Armenians, Foreign Office Minister of 
State Baroness Chalker said today. 
  But she stressed ministers had yet to find any evidence of 
this. 
  Lady Chalker told the Lords at question time: "Officials are 
continuing to investigate the allegations published in THE 
INDEPENDENT (on January 24). 
  "We have no evidence that British mercenaries are fighting 
for Azerbaijan or that British arms have been supplied to that 
country." 
  She said Britain continued to support an international arms 
embargo and could not condone the supply of arms or mercenaries 
to either side. 
  "If there is any evidence of illegal activity, which I 
believe this to be, it should be passed to the police 
authorities for further investigation. 
  "I also believe there is a moral duty on British companies, 
and we sincerely hope no one will supply either arms or 
mercenaries to either side of this conflict or of any other." 

</TEXT>

