<H3> <TI>   Mitterrand Seeks Social Integration of Underprivileged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1202183294 Paris Radio France International in French 1700 
GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1202183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Francois Mitterrand has made an appeal for 
the social integration of the underprivileged urban population. 
The French president, who was in Meyzieu, near Lyon, to open a 
new town hall, said that this is now a major obligation: 
  [Begin Mitterrand recording] Some people are suffering a 
great deal. Let us beware of deep-seated revolt, once reason 
runs out of arguments. In these suburbs, I see an improvement. 
But I see so many employees in different fields living in 
worry, anguish, and perhaps tomorrow, revolt. I want to tell 
you just one thing: Act, act with an idea of what the town 
should be, act with the feeling that if we do not solve this 
problem, we will be passing on to our children in the 21 century 
a destiny which will be much the same as that of so many towns 
around the world. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

