<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Meets Russian Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1202094594 Nicosia KHARAVYI in Greek 12 Feb 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> NC1202094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia KHARAVYI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by L. Dhimitropoulou] </F>
  [Text] Mitrofan Studenikin, chairman of the Russian 
Friendship Association with Cyprus who is visiting our country 
at the head of a three-member delegation, told our paper 
yesterday that the association will propose to the Russian 
parliament the establishment of a parliamentary group for 
contacts with Cyprus. 
  Studenikin reiterated the support of his country and 
association for the Cypriot people and stressed that the purpose 
of their visit is to strengthen traditionally friendly relations 
between the Cypriot and Russian peoples, which have recently 
slackened because of the political developments in Russia. 
  Studenikin stressed, however, that the association continues 
to act and work for the good of both peoples. Many Cypriot 
students, workers, and businessmen who live in Russia have 
frequent contacts with the association while a publications 
exhibition on Cyprus was recently organized in Moscow, which was 
successful. 
  During their stay the delegation has met with Foreign 
Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis, Archbishop Khrisostomos, the 
secretary and other leading members of the Cyprus-Soviet 
Friendship Society, and representatives of the Association of 
Soviet Higher Educational Institutes Graduates and exchanged 
views aimed at further strengthening the relations between the 
Cypriot and Russian peoples. 

</TEXT>

