<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Train Station Explosion Kills 4, Injures 40 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1202113094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1202113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] A bomb exploded at the Tuzla train station in 
Istanbul this morning, killing four and injuring 40 Tuzla 
Infantry School noncommissioned officer cadets. 
  According to a TRT correspondent, Tuzla Infantry School 
cadets arrived en masse at the Tuzla train station to leave on 
their weekend vacation. The students, who were waiting for the 
train to arrive from Gebze, sustained various injuries when one 
or two powerful bombs placed in a garbage bin exploded. 
Forty-four persons, most of whom are seriously injured, were 
taken to various hospitals. Four of the injured died in 
hospital. They have not been identified yet. Officials said 
that the investigation into the incident is continuing in a 
multifaceted way and efforts are under way to identify the 
victims. 
  Istanbul Kartal State Hospital officials announced that they 
need all types of blood and asked those to wish to donate blood 
to come to the hospital. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

